data.content:
**In .NET 11, all your sync methods will throw at runtime.** There is no workaround.

EF Core 11 **fully removed** sync I/O for the Cosmos DB provider. In EF Core 10 you could opt in to sync-over-async, but that opt-in no longer exists — calling any sync API (`ToList()`, `First()`, `Count()`, `SaveChanges()`) **always throws**.

You must convert everything to async:

```csharp
public class ProductRepository
{
    private readonly CosmosDbContext _context;

    public async Task<List<Product>> GetAllAsync()
    {
        return await _context.Products.ToListAsync();
    }

    public async Task<Product> GetByIdAsync(int id)
    {
        return await _context.Products.FirstAsync(p => p.Id == id);
    }

    public async Task<int> GetCountAsync()
    {
        return await _context.Products.CountAsync();
    }

    public async Task SaveAsync(Product product)
    {
        _context.Products.Add(product);
        await _context.SaveChangesAsync();
    }
}
```

This will ripple through your callers — every method up the call chain needs to become `async Task`/`async Task<T>`. There's no way to keep the sync signatures with Cosmos DB in EF Core 11.
